cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) because the paper deals with verification of Markov decision processes, which is a topic related to formal methods and logic in computer science. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because Markov decision processes are commonly used in AI to model decision-making problems, and the paper proposes smart sampling algorithms to improve the efficiency of verifying MDPs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because the paper discusses algorithms for sampling from scheduler space, which is a problem related to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) because the paper deals with verification of concurrent systems, which is a topic related to software engineering. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) because the paper may involve programming languages used to implement the proposed algorithms.
